This paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV) sub-categories, as it proposes a new analytical approximation to the $\chi^2$ kernel that improves performance in image classification and semantic segmentation tasks. The paper also introduces out-of-core principal component analysis (PCA) methods, which are commonly used in machine learning. Additionally, the paper may be relevant to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category, as it proposes a new method for improving performance in machine learning tasks. The paper may also be relevant to the numerical analysis (cs.NA) and software engineering (cs.SD) sub-categories, as it involves developing and implementing new algorithms.
